People walking along Somerton Beach, southwest of Adelaide, found a deceased man aged about 45 lying on the shore on December 1, 1948 . 
  A post-mortem determined the man had died of poisoning but police and coronial investigations were unable to identify the body . 
  The Persian phrase 'ended' was scrawled on the scrap of paper and a woman's telephone number was found in a book . 
  The mystery of the Somerton Man may be solved thanks to the technological advances in DNA testing . 
 